## Navigation

| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| `‚Üë` / `‚Üì` | Move between rows |
| `Enter` | Open disk ‚Üí partition ‚Üí folder |
| `Esc` / `q` | Go back / Quit |
| `r` | Refresh data |

## Screens

```
Main screen (physical disks)
 ‚îî‚îÄ Partition screen (partitions of the selected disk)
      ‚îî‚îÄ Folder browser (du-based folder tree)
           ‚îî‚îÄ Sub-folder browser (navigate deeper)
```

---

## Dev Environment (Docker)

### Prerequisites
- Docker + Docker Compose installed on your server

### Setup

```bash
# 1. Clone / copy the project
cd /opt
git clone ... diskwatch   # or scp from your machine
cd diskwatch

# 2. Make the launcher executable
chmod +x dev.sh

# 3. Build the image (~1 minute)
./dev.sh build

# 4. Enter the dev shell
./dev.sh run
# You are now inside the container ‚Üì

# 5. Run DiskWatch
python diskwatch.py
```

### Live editing
The `./app/` folder is mounted into the container at `/app`.  
Edit `diskwatch.py` on your host with any editor, and re-run `python diskwatch.py` inside the container ‚Äî no rebuild needed.

### Run without entering the shell
```bash
./dev.sh watch
```

---

## Install directly on the server (no Docker)

```bash
# Python 3.10+ required
pip install textual psutil rich

# Run
python /path/to/diskwatch.py
```

To make it available as a command:

```bash
sudo cp app/diskwatch.py /usr/local/bin/diskwatch
sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/diskwatch

# Then just type:
diskwatch
```

